Jones’ defense was impeccable, and I think he definitely won rounds 2, 4 and 5, got some big strikes in and takedowns when it counted the most. Reyes seemed to be coasting through the 5th round, and when you’re the challenger, you can’t let it go to the judges like that. Just like the president, Jones has a sort of incumbent advantage. Could’ve gone either way, though honestly. Both of them deserved it. Great fight.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think when people watch a fight in "real-time", and the challenger puts up a good fight, fans clamor that the challenger won. Everyone likes the underdog story, especially if the champ isn't well liked, but let's be objective.
Round 1 - Clearly Reyes
Round 2 - Clearly Jones
Round 3 - Very Close Round, toss up
Round 4 - Slightly Jones
Round 5 - Clearly Jones

Jones won.
Also, after reading the comments, I was expecting the commentary to be egregiously biased, so I watched the fight without sound, then with sound. I can honestly say that they called the fight beautifully. Completely objective commentary. The bias is from y'all, the fans.
snippet.textOriginal:
I think when people watch a fight in "real-time", and the challenger puts up a good fight, fans clamor that the challenger won. Everyone likes the underdog story, especially if the champ isn't well liked, but let's be objective. 
Round 1 - Clearly Reyes
Round 2 - Clearly Jones
Round 3 - Very Close Round, toss up
Round 4 - Slightly Jones
Round 5 - Clearly Jones

Jones won.
Also, after reading the comments, I was expecting the commentary to be egregiously biased, so I watched the fight without sound, then with sound. I can honestly say that they called the fight beautifully. Completely objective commentary. The bias is from y'all, the fans.

snippet.textDisplay:
I know many saw the match in different way. Well everyone is untitled of own opinion. Even the judges saw it differently.

I for instance, I like Reyes.... He fights well. His strikes were the best so far as far as Jones opponents for the past is concern. But one thing makes the difference... He (as challenger) always backing off most of the round and Jones (the champion) is the more aggressor through out the fight.

I think.... I love both fighter... But I think... It is one of the reason why they give it to Jones... Jones show more energy more pangs... Not to mention he also made some solid shots.

It could be both ways... But then again Jones was the Champion and he was the more aggressor. Basically, even in boxing they will favor the champion...

Just my opinion though.... Peace 🙂
